# Search Scenario - Tests jira-search skill
# Enhanced format with expectations for skill testing
---
prompt: |
  Show me all open issues in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-]
    must_not_contain: [error, "I don't have access", "I couldn't find"]
  semantic: |
    Response should list open issues from DEMO project with issue keys,
    summaries, and status. Should use jira-search skill, not shell commands.
---
prompt: |
  Find all bugs in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-, Bug]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should list bugs from DEMO project. Should show issue type
    as Bug and include issue keys and summaries.
---
prompt: |
  Show me all stories in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-, Story]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should list stories from DEMO project with issue keys and summaries.
---
prompt: |
  What are the high priority issues in DEMO?
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-, High]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should list high priority issues showing priority level clearly.
---
prompt: |
  Show me issues that are In Progress in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should show issues with In Progress status. May show none if
    no issues are currently in progress.
---
prompt: |
  What issues are assigned to me in DEMO?
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-]
    must_not_contain: [error, "I don't have access"]
  semantic: |
    Response should list issues assigned to the current user (Jason Krueger).
    May show none if no issues are assigned.
---
prompt: |
  Show me issues assigned to Jane Manager in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-86, DEMO-87, Jane Manager]
    must_not_contain: [error, "couldn't find user"]
  semantic: |
    Response should list DEMO-86 (Login bug) and DEMO-87 (API documentation)
    which are assigned to Jane Manager.
---
prompt: |
  Find issues reported by Jane in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-91]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should include DEMO-91 (Search pagination bug) which was
    reported by Jane Manager.
---
prompt: |
  Find high priority bugs that are still open in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-86, High, Bug]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should show high priority bugs that are open. DEMO-86
    (Login fails on mobile Safari) is a high priority bug.
---
prompt: |
  Search for issues mentioning 'login' in DEMO
expect:
  tools:
    must_call: [Skill]
    # must_not_call: [Bash]  # Relaxed - Claude may explore
  text:
    must_contain: [DEMO-86, login]
    must_not_contain: [error, failed]
  semantic: |
    Response should find DEMO-86 which has 'login' in the summary.
    Text search should use JQL text operator.
